laboratory_examinations.findings: Minimal dependent atelectasis in the left lower lobe. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. A hypodense lesion measures 0.9 x 0.7 cm in segment 7, may represent a biliary hamartoma, cyst, or hemangioma. No evidence of biliary dilatation. The appendix is retrocecal position, fluid-filled, and dilated measuring a maximum diameter of 1.2 cm with adjacent fatty stranding. No adjacent fluid collection or extraluminal air.
Mixed bacterial flora (>= 3 colony types), consistent with skin and/or genital contamination.
29.4 sec (specific test unspecified, possibly PT or aPTT).
